# __CAMBER_TITLE__

A cambered app. Three commands:

```bash
./gate.sh    # ruff + pytest + camber check; green means done
./run.sh     # http://127.0.0.1:8000
uv run camber new component app/components/<name>   # grow it
```

Working with an agent? Point it at this directory — AGENTS.md is its
onboarding, the gate is its reviewer. No uv? `python -m venv .venv &&
. .venv/bin/activate && pip install -e . --group dev`, then swap `uv run`
for direct commands. Then install uv anyway.
